commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for tracking three types of tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Add support for tracking three types of tasks:
1. ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to
2. Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time
3. Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a
specific date/time

Improve code quality to make code more readable.

Readable code is easier for more people to work on the same project. It
also makes debugging easier in the future.

Let's
* ensure approriate access levels for class fields
* make file paths a constant that can be changed from one spot
* throw exceptions for default branches with no default action
* use the same string building style, especially within the same return
  statement

Changing these things help us adhere to information hiding and catch
errors more effectively.
Improve code quality

Implement extension C-Undo in order to make it easier for users to undo
an action that they may have accidentally done.

Creating a shortcut like this for users helps to increase their
efficiency in using the program.

Let's
* pick out which commands make sense to undo
* create a way to store commands that can be undone, so that we can
  access them in the future if needed
